5,"region":66,"settlement":58,"repository":503,"idno":506,"textLang":508,"facsimile":510,"provenance":53,"letterHeights":515,"publications":516,"zotero":519,"keywords":522,"html":128},"ISic002995","Inscribed altar or statue base",{"_":10},{"_":197,"ana":198,"ref":199},{"_":337,"ana":338,"ref":339,"certainty":340},"altar\n                                    ","#object.altar","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/30.html",{"locus":341,"match":342,"assertedValue":140,"desc":139},"value","../@ana",{"_":344,"ana":345,"ref":346},"limestone","#material.stone.limestone","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/66.html",{"ana":348},"#condition.damaged",{"layout":350},{"p":351,"rs":352,"damage":353},"The inscribed face is maximum 0.26 m high and 0.497 m wide. The text is extremely irregular and uneven in its layout, with letters of varying size and the horizontal of the lines very erratic. The text appears to observe the left margin with some consistency, but is extremely irregular on the right. The full height of the face is employed: the final line is squeezed.",{"_":29,"ana":30,"ref":31},{"ana":354},"#text_condition.incomplete",{"lettering":356,"dimensions":454},[357,358],"The inscription is crudely engraved and inexpertly laid out on the face. The letter forms are primarily distinguished by their irregularity and the poor quality of the engraving. Theta is formed by large circle with single mid-dot; epsilon on occasion has a shorter middle bar; omega is notable in being consistently extremely open, with short horizontal tails (projecting outwards only); omicron is generally full-size, or nearly so, but also smaller; kappa has equal length arms which join the vertical, but do not generally extend fully to the top/bottom of the line; alpha is broad with straight bar; phi has a rounded closed eye; nu on occasion has a shorter right vertical, leaning outwards; sigma is either four straight bars (with top and bottom strokes open beyond the horizontal) or with the top and bottom strokes joined by a single curving stroke; rho is closed, with either a rounded or an angular eye; pi has a shorter right hasta; mu is in one case faint and compressed, in the other broad and composed of four short off vertical strokes; delta is either regular, or with the base line angled down to the right.",{"_":359,"ref":360},"\n                                    Types list:\n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                ",[361,364,367,370,373,376,379,382,385,388,391,394,397,400,403,406,409,412,415,418,421,424,427,430,433,436,439,442,445,448,451],{"_":362,"target":363},"Α type1","https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type1.html",{"_":365,"target":366},"Α type1.2","https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type1.2.html",{"_":368,"target":36